# jobhound_core Development Guidelines

Spec-driven workflow via `.specify` and `/speckit.*` commands. Update this file when plans change (or run the Specify update script when wired).

## Active Technologies

- Go 1.24 — standard library first; `net/http` / `html` / `encoding/json` for Tier-1 API and static fetchers
- `github.com/PuerkitoBio/goquery` for HTML sources (Tier 2)
- `github.com/go-rod/rod` + session cookies file for LinkedIn (Tier 3)
- PostgreSQL + GORM + migrations — jobs, history, profile, dedup
- Temporal — workflows/activities for manual runs and scheduled events
- Claude API for scoring; Telegram Bot API for delivery
- Local: Docker Compose (Postgres + Temporal); production: GCP (see `specs/000-epic-overview`)

## Project Structure

```text
cmd/agent/              # agent binary (wiring)
cmd/migrate/            # SQL migrations CLI
internal/domain/        # shared domain types (e.g. Job)
internal/config/        # config shape; secrets only from env (see Makefile help)
internal/db/            # Postgres open, pool; integration-tagged migration tests
internal/jobs/          # jobs module: contract, storage (GORM)
internal/pipeline/      # collect/filter/score pipeline: contract, impl, mock
tests/integration/      # optional cross-module integration suites (same `integration` build tag)
migrations/             # SQL migration files
```

**Modules**: each feature area under `internal/<name>/` exposes contracts at the module root (`contract.go`, etc.); implementations in `impl/`, `storage/`, `handlers/` as needed. Compose processes in `cmd/`. See `.specify/memory/constitution.md` for the full module folder table.

## Testing

- **Unit**: `*_test.go` next to the code, **same package** as the implementation (idiomatic Go).
- **Integration**: `//go:build integration`; run `make test-integration` or `go test -tags=integration ./...` (needs env such as `JOBHOUND_DATABASE_URL` where applicable).
- Do not rely on `export_test.go` or external `tests/unit/...` trees for ordinary package tests.

## Commands

- `make build` — compile `./cmd/agent` to `bin/agent`
- `make run` — build and run agent
- `make test` — `go test ./...` (excludes `integration`-tagged tests)
- `make test-integration` — `go test -tags=integration ./...`
- `make fmt` / `make vet` / `make tidy`

## Code Style

- Go 1.24 conventions; interfaces on module boundaries in `internal/<feature>/contract.go` (or split files); persistence under `internal/<feature>/storage`
- No secrets or real `.env` in git — see `make help` for documented env variable names
- Table-driven tests where behavior branches; keep `main` thin

